<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Jhihad on 05-27-2001 10:23 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Not really sure about this.  One way to deal with the Dot is to have everyone put 1 junk buff on top slot, followed by a insta cast buff (like jboots, shrunken goblin skull earring, etc.).  Put 1-2 int casters in each of the tanks groups.  Before you pull you would have everyone get their 2 top buff dispelled by nullify/anull.  Than everyone would click their insta cast item.  That would make it so everyone has 1 instacast buff at top and one Emply slot.  When you fight, people would call out for dispells, and the designated dispellers (the int casters most likely) would dispell the people in the groups.  The DOT would take the 2nd slot on your buff columns, and when you get dispelled you would lose the DOT and the insta cast item.  Than the person just clicks their insta cast item.  This would allow people to be fully buffed and keep their buffs while allowing a slot for themselves to get dispelled.  Still would be a long fight, and making the int casters dispellers would make the fight totally dependent on melee dmg+pets but all velious fights are like that basically.  The problem is that Rumbleroot spams the DOT, so you probably need 2 dispellers per group to ensure that you take minimal dmg.

I havent really dont POG since a long time ago, just this is how I would try to tackle the DOT problem.  Take note that we only have evil races in our guild, so bards really wouldnt be an option.

------------------
Jhihad Daemonwrath, High Priest
Xanit K'ven, Vallon Zek</TEXTAREA>
